<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="448" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1747</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Guaranty Trust Company of New
                                    York</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-15"><hi rend="italic">March 15,
                                1927</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received March 16.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">513–27</seg>
                            <lb/>
                            <seg rendition="#left">Foreign Department</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: We have the pleasure to acknowledge
                            receipt of your communication of the 12th instant, and in view of the
                            contents thereof we have advised the President of Nicaragua, through the
                            Manager of the National Bank of Nicaragua, Inc., that we, in conjunction
                            with Messrs. J. &amp; W. Seligman &amp; Co., are prepared to make a loan
                            of $1,000,000.—to the Republic of Nicaragua for the purposes, and under
                                <pb facs="0535" n="433" xml:id="pg_433"/> the terms and conditions
                            indicated in the memorandum of the 11th of March, 1927, which was sent
                            to you with our letter of the same date.</p>
                        <p>We are [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">Guaranty Trust Company of New
                                    York</hi>,<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. F.
                                Loree</hi></signed>, <hi rend="italic">Vice President</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>